{
  "name": "RPlog_Declan_and_the_Jedi",
  "title": "Declan and the Jedi",
  "summary": "In the quiet evening hours at Karrde's hidden base on Myrkr, the former Imperial intelligence officer Declan Rahn works at a data terminal in the maintenance hangar when the Jedi Jessalyn Valios and the spacer Drew Carvallo wander over after dinner. Declan, ever the wary analyst, quietly probes Jessalyn about her unexpected past as a New Republic flight technician before her late initiation into the Jedi, and about how the Jedi are funded these days. He reveals that his own Rahn family once donated heavily to the Jedi Council before its fall, and frankly states his wish that the galaxy might one day govern itself without Force-wielders controlling it. Jessalyn gently counters that the Jedi seek not to control but to prevent others from seizing control, defending their role as guardians of wisdom, freedom, and justice. Declan offers a measured compliment on her reluctant, selfless approach to her calling before Jessalyn excuses herself for the evening.",
